wikipedia_page.main: George Corbett (11 May 1925 – June 1999) is an English former professional footballer who played as a left back and left winger.

response: Robert Corbett (16 March 1922 – October 1988) was an English footballer who played as a defender. He was the brother of George Corbett, also a professional footballer. He began playing at non-league club Throckley Welfare, later moving to Newcastle United and made his professional debut in 1946 against Barnsley F.C. after the conclusion of the Second World War. He was sold to neighbouring club Middlesbrough in 1951 for £9000, where he made 92 appearances over five seasons. He finished his career with a two-year spell at Northampton Town.
George Corbett is the name of:
*George Corbett (American football) (1908–1990), American football running back for the Chicago Bears
